      caption: "\u{1F537} OWNERSHIP RENOUNCED\n\u2726 Admin Keys Burned \u2014 No Human Can Change the Rules\n\nIn the world of smart contracts, 'ownership renounced' is the gold standard of decentralization. TurboLoop's contract ownership has been permanently transferred to the dead address (0x000...dead), meaning the admin keys that could modify, pause, or interfere with the contract have been irreversibly destroyed. There are no backdoors. No emergency functions. No pause mechanisms. No upgrade paths. The contract executes exactly as written, autonomously and indefinitely, without any possibility of human intervention. This isn't a temporary measure or a promise \u2014 it's a permanent, on-chain, verifiable fact. Once renounced, ownership can never be reclaimed. The code is the law, forever.\n\n\u2705 Key Highlights:\n\u2022 Ownership transferred to dead address: 0x000...dead\n\u2022 Admin keys permanently and irreversibly burned\n\u2022 No backdoors, no emergency functions, no pause capability\n\u2022 Contract executes autonomously \u2014 no human intervention possible\n\u2022 Verifiable on BscScan \u2014 check the owner address yourself\n\n\u{1F48E} Code is law. Forever. No exceptions. No reversals.\n\n\u{1F310} turboloop.io",
